📘 UNIQA RFP – Master Memory Jogger (Markdown)
A portable, context‑complete reference for any LLM

#️⃣ 1. What the PPT Contains (Exact Content Summary)
1.1 Overall Ask
UNIQA Insurance Group has issued an RFP to build three AI MVPs, each lasting 3 months, starting July 2026.

The PPT defines three MVPs:

MVP 1 – Claims Processing Automation
Problems Identified in PPT:

Early-stage claims processing is manual, slow, and inconsistent.

Email-based submissions require human triage.

Data extraction and routing are error-prone.

Need for low-risk, controlled automation with human oversight.

What the PPT Requests:

AI-supported automation for early-stage claims.

Three use cases:

Legal Protection (Consultation Insurance)

Car Casco Claim Registration

MTPL Recourse Detection

Email intake → AI extraction → enrichment → routing → claim creation.

Human-in-the-loop escalation.

Integration with claims backend.

Azure-based deployment.

Full auditability, compliance, modularity.

MVP 2 – Corporate Underwriting Assistant
Problems Identified in PPT:

Underwriters lack fast, AI-supported decision tools.

Risk assessment requires data from multiple systems.

No unified knowledge representation.

What the PPT Requests:

AI-powered Underwriting Assistant.

Integrations with:

CBN

Inquiry Manager

Large Loss Database

GEAM

Google Maps

Knowledge Graph for risk data.

AI agents for:

Risk assessment

Compliance checks

Wording comparison

Underwriter Decision Dashboard.

Explainability, provenance, auditability.

Azure-based scalable architecture.

Training + adoption support.

MVP 3 – Agentic AI Platform
Problems Identified in PPT:

UNIQA lacks a unified, governed AI platform.

Need for reusable, scalable, compliant AI capabilities.

What the PPT Requests:

Group-level AI platform with:

Shared core model

Country-specific integrations

Integration with enterprise systems:

IAM

Data platforms

BPM/workflow

Governance layer:

Policy enforcement

Content filtering

Audit logging

Knowledge ingestion + retrieval

Model abstraction layer

Observability + monitoring

Developer enablement framework

Co-build model with knowledge transfer

Azure-based scalable architecture

1.2 Skills Required (from PPT)
AI/ML Architect

ML Engineer

Data Scientist

Data Engineer

MLOps

Integration Engineer

Backend Engineer

AI Platform Engineer

Product Owner

Business Analyst

UX/UI

Data Privacy & Compliance

QA

Security

PM/Delivery Lead

Transformation Consultant

Knowledge Transfer Lead

