#️⃣ 4. Conclusions From Our Discussion
4.1 What the Three MVPs Represent
MVP 1 = Operational automation (claims).

MVP 2 = Decision intelligence (underwriting).

MVP 3 = Foundational AI platform (agentic + governed).

4.2 How They Fit Together
MVP1 and MVP2 are use cases.

MVP3 is the platform that will eventually host and scale these use cases.

MVP3 must be designed with MVP1 and MVP2 as the first tenants.

4.3 What Your Role Actually Is
You are not building the MVPs.
You are designing the plan for how they will be built.

Your deliverables include:

Solution architecture for each MVP

Effort estimation

Delivery timeline

Team structure

Risks & assumptions

Integration approach

Azure architecture

Governance & compliance approach

Human-in-the-loop design

Knowledge graph design (for MVP2)

Agentic platform blueprint (for MVP3)

4.4 Why We Need a Clear Handoff Logic
We discussed the idea of:

First layer: simple rule-based acceptance/rejection

Second layer: deeper reasoning when rules fail

Third layer: platform-level orchestration

This ensures:

No hallucination

No forced answers

Clear escalation path

Predictable behavior

#️⃣ 5. Tech Stack We Agreed On (and Why)
5.1 Azure as the Core Cloud
Why:

UNIQA already uses Azure (explicit in PPT).

Enterprise compliance + IAM integration is easier.

Native support for ML, agents, and observability.

5.2 AI Components
Azure OpenAI (for LLMs + agents)

Azure ML (for training, pipelines, monitoring)

Azure Cognitive Search (for retrieval)

Knowledge Graph (Neo4j or Azure Cosmos DB Gremlin API)

Why:

PPT explicitly requires knowledge ingestion, retrieval, explainability, auditability.

5.3 Integration Layer
Azure API Management

Azure Functions

Event Grid / Service Bus

Why:

Required for backend integration in claims and underwriting.

5.4 Data Layer
Azure Data Lake

Azure SQL / Cosmos DB

Azure Purview (governance)

Why:

PPT requires data provenance, auditability, compliance.

5.5 Platform Layer (MVP 3)
Model abstraction layer

Policy enforcement

Content filtering

Audit logging

Observability (Azure Monitor, App Insights)

Why:

PPT explicitly lists these as required capabilities.

